Vice President Biden spoke with Iraqi Prime Minister Haider Al-Abadi to discuss political and security developments in Iraq. They emphasized the importance of continuing the fight against ISIL and reviewed efforts to enhance security in Baghdad. They also discussed the urgency of humanitarian and stabilization efforts for the Mosul campaign and the need for international support. Prime Minister Abadi thanked the Vice President for the U.S. Government's role in mobilizing over $2 billion in support for Iraq. The Vice President expressed continued U.S. support for a unified and democratic Iraq and encouraged cooperation between the Iraqi government and the Kurdistan Regional Government in defeating ISIL. Both leaders highlighted ongoing successes as a sign of the strong partnership between Iraq and the United States.